ss=\"ws-header wst-header-structure wst-unknown wst-header ws-header ws-noexport noprint dynlayout-exempt\"><div class=\"wst-header-mainblock wst-unknown-mainblock headertemplate\"><div class=\"wst-header-back searchaux wst-unknown-back\"><div class=\"wst-header-back-arrow\">←</div><div class=\"wst-header-back-link\"><a href=\"//en.wikisource.org/wiki/Sacred_Books_of_the_East/Volume_3/The_Shu/Part_5/Book_1/Section_3\" title=\"Sacred Books of the East/Volume 3/The Shu/Part 5/Book 1/Section 3\">Book I, Section 3</a></div></div><div class=\"wst-header-central-cell wst-unknown-central-cell\"><span class=\"wst-header-title wst-unknown-title\"><span class=\"wst-header-title-text\"><a href=\"//en.wikisource.org/wiki/Sacred_Books_of_the_East\" title=\"Sacred Books of the East\">Sacred Books of the East</a>, <a href=\"//en.wikisource.org/wiki/Sacred_Books_of_the_East/Volume_3\" title=\"Sacred Books of the East/Volume 3\">Vol. III</a>, <a href=\"//en.wikisource.org/wiki/Sacred_Books_of_the_East/Volume_3/The_Shu\" title=\"Sacred Books of the East/Volume 3/The Shu\">The Shû King</a></span><br class=\"wst-header-title-break\"><span class=\"contributor-text\">translated by&nbsp;<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"//en.wikisource.org/wiki/Author:James_Legge\" title=\"Author:James Legge\">James Legge</a></span></span><div class=\"header-section-text\">Part V, Book II: The Speech at Mû</div></span></div><div class=\"wst-header-forward searchaux wst-unknown-forward\"><div class=\"wst-header-forward-link\"><a href=\"//en.wikisource.org/wiki/Sacred_Books_of_the_East/Volume_3/The_Shu/Part_5/Book_3\" title=\"Sacred Books of the East/Volume 3/The Shu/Part 5/Book 3\">Book III</a></div><div class=\"wst-header-forward-arrow\">→</div></div></div><div class=\"ws-noexport\" id=\"ws-data\" style=\"speak:none\"><span id=\"ws-article-id\">2326421</span><span id=\"ws-title\"><a href=\"//en.wikisource.org/wiki/Sacred_Books_of_the_East\" title=\"Sacred Books of the East\">Sacred Books of the East</a>, <a href=\"//en.wikisource.org/wiki/Sacred_Books_of_the_East/Volume_3\" title=\"Sacred Books of the East/Volume 3\">Vol. III</a>, <a href=\"//en.wikisource.org/wiki/Sacred_Books_of_the_East/Volume_3/The_Shu\" title=\"Sacred Books of the East/Volume 3/The Shu\">The Shû King</a> — Part V, Book II: The Speech at Mû</span><span id=\"ws-translator\">James Legge</span></div></div>\n<div class=\"prp-pages-output\" lang=\"en\">\n<span><span class=\"pagenum ws-pagenum\" id=\"131\" data-page-number=\"131\" data-page-name=\"Page:Sacred Books of the East - Volume 3.djvu/165\" data-page-index=\"165\" data-page-quality=\"4\" title=\"Page:Sacred_Books_of_the_East_-_Volume_3.djvu/165\"><span id=\"pageindex_165\" class=\"pagenum-inner ws-noexport\">​</span></span></span><div class=\"wst-dhr\" style=\"visibility:hidden; line-height:100%;\">&nbsp;</div>\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r15620827\">.mw-parser-output .wst-center{text-align:center;margin:0 auto}.mw-parser-output .wst-center.wst-center-nomargin>p{margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0}</style><div class=\"wst-center tiInherit\">\n<p><span class=\"smallcaps\" style=\"font-variant:small-caps;\">Book II. The Speech at <style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r14767791\">.mw-parser-output .wst-tooltip{cursor:help;border-bottom:thin dotted cornflowerblue}.mw-parser-output .wst-tooltip-nodash{border-bottom:none}</style><span class=\"wst-tooltip wst-tooltip-dash\" title=\"Mù\">Mû</span>.</span>\n</p>\n</div>\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r15431454\">.mw-parser-output .wst-size-block{line-height:1.4}.mw-parser-output .wst-size-block p{font-size:inherit}.mw-parser-output .wst-xx-smaller{font-size:58%}.mw-parser-output .wst-x-smaller{font-size:69%}.mw-parser-output .wst-smaller{font-size:83%}.mw-parser-output .wst-fine{line-height:1.4;font-size:92%}.mw-parser-output .wst-m-larger{font-size:110%}.mw-parser-output .wst-larger{font-size:120%}.mw-parser-output .wst-x-larger{font-size:144%}.mw-parser-output .wst-xx-larger{font-size:182%}.mw-parser-output .wst-xxx-larger{font-size:207%}.mw-parser-output .wst-xxxx-larger{font-size:249%}</style><div class=\"wst-size-block wst-smaller wst-smaller-block\">\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r14893080\">.mw-parser-output .wst-hanging-indent{margin-left:2em;text-indent:-2em}.mw-parser-output .wst-hanging-indent p,.mw-parser-output .wst-hanging-indent li,.mw-parser-output .wst-hanging-indent dd{text-indent:inherit;margin-left:0}.mw-parser-output .wst-hanging-indent li{text-indent:inherit;margin-left:0}.mw-parser-output .wst-hanging-indent.wst-hanging-indent-mid p:first-child,.mw-parser-output .wst-hanging-indent.wst-hanging-indent-mid li:first-child,.mw-parser-output .wst-hanging-indent.wst-hanging-indent-mid dd:first-child{text-indent:0}.mw-parser-output .wst-div-col .wst-hanging-indent p:nth-child(1){margin-top:0}.mw-parser-output .wst-hanging-indent-mid>.wst-toc-dotcell:first-child{text-indent:0}</style><div class=\"wst-hanging-indent\">\n<p><span class=\"smallcaps\" style=\"font-variant:small-caps;\">It</span> is the morning of the day of battle, for which the king has prepared his host by the three speeches of the last Book. Once more he addresses his confederate princes, his officers, and his men. He sets forth more briefly the intolerable wickedness of Shâu, and instructs and warns his troops how they are to behave in the fight.\n</p><p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muye_District\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Muye District\">Mû</a> was in the south of the present district of <i>Kh</i>î, department <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weihui\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Weihui\">Wei-hui</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henan\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Henan\">Ho-nan</a>, a tract of open country stretching into the district of <i>K</i>î, and at no great distance from <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yinxu\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Yinxu\">the capital</a> of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/King_Zhou_of_Shang\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:King Zhou of Shang\">Shâu</a>.\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r15690401\">.mw-parser-output .wst-anchor:target{background-color:rgba(100,149,237,0.1);color:var(--color-base,#202122);outline:1px solid cornflowerblue}</style><span id=\"ch1\" title=\"Anchor:ch1\" class=\"wst-anchor\">1.</span> The time was the grey dawn of the day <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r14767791\"><span class=\"wst-tooltip wst-tooltip-dash\" title=\"Jiǎzǐ\"><i>K</i>iâ-<span style=\"line-height: 50%;\"><style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r13786851\">.mw-parser-output .blackletter{font-family:\"UnifrakturMaguntia\",\"UnifrakturCook\",\"Unifraktur\",serif;font-size:113%}.mw-parser-output .blackletter-mode-0{font-feature-settings:\"cv01\",\"cv02\",\"cv03\",\"cv04\",\"cv05\",\"cv06\",\"cv07\",\"cv08\",\"cv09\",\"cv10\"}.mw-parser-output .blackletter-mode-2{font-feature-settings:\"cv08\"}.mw-parser-output .blackletter-mode-3{font-feature-settings:\"cv01\"}.mw-parser-output .blackletter-mode-4{font-feature-settings:\"cv01\",\"cv08\"}.mw-parser-output .blackletter-mode-5{font-feature-settings:\"cv01\",\"cv08\",\"cv04\"2}</style><span lang=\"en-Latf\" class=\"blackletter blackletter-mode-\" style=\"-webkit-font-feature-settings:'cv01', 'cv02', 'cv03', 'cv04', 'cv05', 'cv06', 'cv07', 'cv08', 'cv09', 'cv10'; -ms-font-feature-settings:'cv01', 'cv02', 'cv03', 'cv04', 'cv05', 'cv06', 'cv07', 'cv08', 'cv09', 'cv10';\">z</span></span>ze</span>. On that morning the king came to the open country of Mû, in the borders of <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r14767791\"><span class=\"wst-tooltip wst-tooltip-dash\" title=\"Shāng\">Shang</span>, and addressed his army. In his left hand he carried a battle-axe, yellow with gold, and in his right he held a white ensign, which he waved, saying, 'Far are ye come, ye men of the western regions!' He added, 'Ah! ye hereditary rulers of my friendly states; ye managers of affairs,—the Ministers of Instruction, of War, and of Works; the great officers subordinate to these, and the many other officers; the master of my body-guards; the captains of thousands and captains of hundreds; and ye, O men of <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r14767791\"><span class=\"wst-tooltip wst-tooltip-dash\" title=\"Yōng\">Yung</span>, <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r14767791\"><span class=\"wst-tooltip wst-tooltip-dash\" title=\"Shǔ\">Shû</span>, <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r14767791\"><span class=\"wst-tooltip wst-tooltip-dash\" title=\"Qiāng\"><i>K</i>iang</span>, <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r14767791\"><span class=\"wst-tooltip wst-tooltip-dash\" title=\"Máo\">Mâo</span>, <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r14767791\"><span class=\"wst-tooltip wst-tooltip-dash\" title=\"Wēi\">Wei</span>, <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r14767791\"><span class=\"wst-tooltip wst-tooltip-dash\" title=\"Lú\">Lû</span>, <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r14767791\"><span class=\"wst-tooltip wst-tooltip-dash\" title=\"Péng\">Phang</span>, and <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r14767791\"><span class=\"wst-tooltip wst-tooltip-dash\" title=\"Pú\">Pho</span><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\">[</span>1<span class=\"cite-bracket\">]</span></a></sup>, lift up your lances, join your shields, raise your spears:—I have a speech to make.'\n</p>\n<div class=\"__nop wst-nop\"></div>\n<p> <span><span class=\"pagenum ws-pagenum\" id=\"132\" data-page-number=\"132\" data-page-name=\"Page:Sacred Books of the East - Volume 3.djvu/166\" data-page-index=\"166\" data-page-quality=\"4\" title=\"Page:Sacred_Books_of_the_East_-_Volume_3.djvu/166\"><span id=\"pageindex_166\" class=\"pagenum-inner ws-noexport\">​</span></span></span><link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r15690401\"><span id=\"ch2\" title=\"Anchor:ch2\" class=\"wst-anchor\">2.</span> The king (then) said, 'The ancients have said, \"The hen does not announce the morning. The crowing of a hen in the morning (indicates) the subversion of the family.\" Now <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r14767791\"><span class=\"wst-tooltip wst-tooltip-dash\" title=\"Shòu\">Shâu</span>, the king of Shang, follows only the words of his wife. In his blindness he has neglected the sacrifices which he ought to offer, and makes no response (for the favours that he has received);* he has also cast off his paternal and maternal relations, not treating them properly. They are only the vagabonds from all quarters, loaded with crimes, whom he honours and exalts, whom he employs and trusts, making them great officers and high nobles, so that they can tyrannize over the people, and exercise their villainies in the cities of Shang.\n</p><p>'Now, I, <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r14767791\"><span class=\"wst-tooltip wst-tooltip-dash\" title=\"Fā\">Fâ</span>, am simply executing respectfully the punishment appointed by Heaven.* In to-day's business do not advance more than six or seven steps, and then stop and adjust your ranks;—my brave men, be energetic! Do not exceed four blows, five blows, six blows, or seven blows, and then stop and adjust your ranks;—my brave men, be energetic! Display a martial bearing. Be like tigers and panthers, like bears and grisly bears,—(here) in the borders of Shang. Do not rush on these who fly (to us in submission), but receive them to serve our western land;—my brave men, be energetic! If you be not energetic (in all these matters), you will bring destruction on yourselves.' \n</p>\n</div>\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r15431518\">.mw-parser-output .wst-rule{background-color:currentcolor;color:inherit;width:auto;margin:2px auto 2px auto;height:1px;overflow:hidden}.mw-parser-output .wst-rule.wst-rule-left{margin-left:0}.mw-parser-output .wst-rule.wst-rule-right{margin-right:0}.mw-parser-output .wst-rule.__uirule{background-color:#a2a9b1;color:inherit;border:0;margin-top:0.2em;margin-bottom:0.2em}</style><hr class=\"wst-rule wst-rule-center\" style=\"color:inherit;\">\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r14922110\">.mw-parser-output .wst-smallrefs{font-size:83%;clear:both;line-height:1.25;margin-top:0.3em}.mw-parser-output .wst-smallrefs ol.references{margin-top:0}.mw-parser-output .wst-smallrefs-ruled{border-top:1px solid;padding-top:0.3em}.mw-parser-output .wst-smallrefs ol.references.uksi{margin-top:0;list-style-type:lower-alpha}.mw-parser-output .wst-smallrefs ol.references.uksi li::marker{font-weight:bold}</style>\n<div class=\"prp-pages-output\"><div class=\"reflist wst-smallrefs\" style=\"\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">These are the names of eight different tribes or confederations of tribes of the south and west. We are to look for their sites in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sichuan\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Sichuan\">Sze-<i>kh</i>üan</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yunnan\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Yunnan\">Yün-nan</a>, and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hubei\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Hubei\">Hû-pei</a>. They were, no doubt, an important portion of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/King_Wu_of_Zhou\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:King Wu of Zhou\">Wû</a>'s army, but only as auxiliaries. It is too much to ascribe, as some have done, the overthrow of <a href=\"//en.wikisource.org/wiki/Portal:Shang_dynasty\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Portal:Shang dynasty\">Shang</a> to an irruption of barbarous people from the west.</span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw‐web.codfw.main‐6fc5bb98bd‐p6jgw\nCached time: 20260502235512\nCache expiry: 2592000\nCache expiry source: Module:Header (os.date(%Y))\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: [vary‐page‐id, vary‐revision‐sha1]\nCPU time usage: 0.122 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.191 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 744/1000000\nRevision size: 403/2097152 bytes\nPost‐expand include size: 16325/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 3199/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 18/100\nExpensive parser function count: 3/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 1/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 16040/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.041/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1834831/52428800 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/500\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  182.390      1 -total\n 42.95%   78.332      1 Page:Sacred_Books_of_the_East_-_Volume_3.djvu/165\n 37.61%   68.604      1 Template:Header\n 15.36%   28.008     13 Template:Tooltip\n 10.06%   18.349      1 Template:Smaller_block\n 10.03%   18.296      1 Template:Center\n  7.57%   13.800      1 Template:Bl/il\n  6.45%   11.758      2 Template:Anchor+\n  5.47%    9.972      1 Template:Line-height\n  4.47%    8.149      1 Template:Blackletter\n-->\n\n<!-- Render ID 5b7ffff7-4682-11f1-9cab-4b69d4f46be1 -->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwikisource:pcache:2326421:|#|:idhash:canonical and timestamp 20260502235512 and revision id 11773919. Rendering was triggered because: page_view\n -->\n</div>"
